Sample was collected after days of rainy weather.  Mayflies emerging during sampling.  Lake level: no benchmark on the lake
Very windy and rough on May 15- as were previous several days- weather is clear and sunny- no plant growth or algal growth evident- ice went off on the 1st of the week.
Somewhat stormy- but sunny- during collection.  Heavy emergence of may flies during past several days.
Clear day- following 1" of rain storm.
Collection made on a very windy day.
Clear day- last week we had about 5 inches of rain- the lake is somewhat higher than normal for this time of the year.
Ice off 2 weeks ago- weather is very windy- cloudy.
Sunny- windy- clear water- several cormorants on the lake.
Clear- week of very hot- dry weather.
Partly cloudy- somewhat windy- water level low due to dry weather conditions for past 4-6 weeks.
Cloudy- gentle breeze- some ducks on the lake.
Sample taken following a 2 day period of rain.
Note: tannins washed into lake from evergreen swamp during several recent and intense rain storms may have improved water clarity at this time.
Partly cloudy- 1.25" of rain several days prior to sampling.
hazy sun- moderate north wind.  pH 8.8
Cloudy- water somewhat rough Cloudy- water somewhat rough
Sunny- windy. Sunny- windy. Sunny- windy.
Partly sunny- pleasant.  Kevin and Cindy Wienkers accompanied me and observed the water sampling procedures.
Cloudy- quiet.  Kevin and Cindy Wienkers accompanied me to collect and process the water samples.
It had rained most of the day and it  was both windy and foggy. This was the only day that I could be up to take the samples before our trip out of the country.
Sunny day- Kevin and Aaron went out to collect the samples. The water level was high and flowing over the dam. We have had a lot of rain.
Kevin collected the sample along with our son Aaron. It was sunny- 80F- SW winds at 5 knots. The water temp was 77F. They saw about a 9" bass.  pH 6.5
Kevin + Aaron collected the samples.  It was sunny- 68F- winds from South 10 knots.

column1: We collected additional samples per Ashley's request. The acidified deionized (blank) water was pH 2.5. The deionized water alone was pH 5.0.
Previous days had been heavy winds so the water was stirred up some. There was some floating millfoil.
Several young ducklings with parents were spotted in the water and a kingfisher.

column2: Air temperature 87F- winds W 5 mph- water temperature 72F.  Clear- sunny- perfect day in Door County.

column1: The chlorophyll tested a little higher than normal for June.

No reading June 2013 but July 2013 was 4.49 ug/l This could be due to the transportation of the tube. The tube was collected- put on ice in a cooler- and transported one hour to our main home.  It was then frozen until being sent out the next morning. Normally we collect the tube- freeze it at the cabin- and then transport it frozen on ice in a cooler. It will be interesting to see what the July sample tests.

column2: Air temperature 76F- water temperature 75F- winds N 10 mph- sunny- beautiful day but a little windy.
Air temp 78F-  winds SSE 6 mph- partly sunny.

column1: Water level is lower than it was this spring.
Appears to be a lot of weeds at about 6' in the area of the 11" deep hole where we normally sample.  We have had several weeks of unusually hot temps with very little rain.

column2: The twins were home from college and helped Kevin to collect the first sample of the season.  The air was 68F- water 61F- light winds- sunny- pH 7- and the water was flowing over the dam.  It couldn't have been a nicer Memorial weekend day in Door Co. The ice went off the lake on March 30th.

Son Aaron was home from Stanford so he got to assist in the sample collection for the first time.  Air temp was 72F- sunny- light winds- pH 6- and the water was flowing over the dam.  Lovely day in Door Co- could not have been a nicer Father's day weekend.
Sunny- air temp was 71F- the winds were N 10 mph.  We recently had a lot of rain- the water level was extremely high.

column1: Water temp was 74F- the water color was green at the time of collecting the sample but it looked better a couple of weeks later. The pH was 6. Was an enjoyable day for sailing.

column2: Beautiful day on the lake. Air temp 76F and windy  Water was clear and blue green.  pH 6.0.

column1: The water was clear and very high. We just had 32" of snow the weekend of April 14/15.
The ice went off the lake on April 28. This is the latest in our present recording- 1998-present- that ice went off the lake. The latest date previously was April 29- 1914.
We then had an unusually hot Memorial Day weekend EVEN in Door Co.

column2: The air temp was 77F- the water temp was 76F. The water was clear and green. The water level was high.
Water temp 75F and clear. Lake level was low.
It was sunny.  Air temperature was 74F- winds were N at 8 mph.  The water temperature was 80F and the level was low. There was hardly any water in the creek. There was a lot of plant growth. pH 6

It was a pleasant + sunny day in Door Co. The air temperature was 65F- the winds were light and variable- S + E. The water level is high. The water is very clear- you can see the bottom. The lake temperature was 63F.

It was a pleasant + sunny day in Door County. We finally had a break from the rain.  The air temperature was 65F. The winds were light and from the E. The water level is still high. The lake temperature was 63F.
It was a lovely sunny day in Door County.  The air temp was 74F- the winds were SSE 12 mph. The water temp was 78F.

The air temp. was 68F. It was sunny with winds out of the E at 8 mph. A beautiful Door Co weekend. The water temp was 72F.  The water level had been running high but is now normal for this time of the year even though the creek has gotten pretty low.

It was a beautiful day on the lake. It was sunny with an air temp of 74F. The water was very clear and is the highest it has been in years.The water temp was 64F.  I have been getting reports of Sturgeon getting in over the fish grate at the dam on Heins Creek due to the high water levels. We saw several small mouth bass fish beds while kayaking.
Beautiful sunny day on the lake. The air temp was 73F. The water temp was also 73F. The winds were calm.

Cloudy day on the lake with rain approaching. The air temp was 82F- water 78F- winds light but picking up. Due to Covid 19 the SLH (State Lab of Hygiene) has not been doing any water quality analysis. We have continued to collect the specimens and have them frozen with acid being added to the phosphorus sample to preserve it and the chlorophyll filtered. The chlorophyll sample can only be submitted frozen.
Sunny day at the lake. It has been hot and very dry but we got rain yesterday.  Air temp 79F- water temp 76F with calm winds.
